A program that simulates a dungeon with a variety of monsters who follow specific behavioral patterns

The number of monsters can be specified by passing a number after the --nummon switch

Valid switch examples:
	./dungeon --save --load 00.rlg327 --nummon 4 (how to correctly pass a location)
	./dungeon --nummon 4 (only using nummon switch)
	./dungeon --nummon --save --load 4 (switches can be in any order)

Invalid switch examples
	./dungeon --save --load --nummon 00.rlg327 10 (location must be before nummon)
	./dungeon --nummon 4 --save --load 00.rlg327 (location still has to be before nummon)